reviews.text: Fairly scenic, sheltered and leafy station with evidence of its former life on a double track line, though now a single platform suffices to meet demand. Solid brick, open-fronted waiting shelter with ticket machine and – somewhat surprisingly as these are rather thin on the ground nowadays – a payphone. Very small car park, which usually has a few free spaces despite its diminutive size, immediately adjacent to platform.
A basic railway station on the scenic Esk Valley Line. Steam trains pass through from time to time.
